  "body": "Currently, if a user clones a repo but forgets `--recurse`, they can only get the dependencies by manually using git or using `forge update`. The issue is if a user updates, it updates to the latest version of that submodule when it downloads. I propose `forge install` with no parameters redownloads dependencies *without* updating the dependency.",
